This paper is about generating keyphrases for scientific articles using GANs. The most relevant sub-category is likely to be cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as text generation and summarization. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques as it generates keyphrases based on the content of the article. Additionally, the use of GANs involves machine learning and deep learning techniques, which are commonly associated with sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper's focus on generating diverse keyphrases may also be relevant to the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
